{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"b452bb07-679a-43ce-af49-3965e46c16ba","content":"Use the `--filter` option:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter FullyQualifiedName~ReportExporterTests\n```\n\nOr filter by class name directly:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter ClassName=ReportExporterTests\n```\n\nThe `~` operator means \"contains\", so the first form matches any test whose fully qualified name includes `ReportExporterTests`. The `=` operator requires an exact match on the class name.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"65715cdf-c3b7-4d80-a468-d69809b5ae24","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to know how to run only a specific test class using `dotnet test`. This is a straightforward question I can answer directly.","outputTokens":154,"requestId":"A042:2FE433:D52D6A:F9BD87:69FE8D5C"},"id":"905e706d-ccaa-43ec-8557-1baa78742726","timestamp":"2026-05-09T01:26:56.583Z","parentId":"00d6f6b7-f3d0-4c61-a4f3-4a64eb9eedf0"}
